<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Self-Sufficiency Progress Marks Minfar Council </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2203003494 Havana Cuba Vision Network in Spanish 2320 GMT 
21 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2203003494 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Cuba Vision Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Army General Raul Castro Ruz, second secretary of 
the Communist Party of Cuba and Revolutionary Armed Forces 
minister, presided over the Minfar's [Ministry of the 
Revolutionary Armed Forces] expanded military council, at which 
a final assessment was made of all the activities carried out 
during 1993 by the three armies and of all the weapons that 
defend the national territory. This account led to the 
conclusion that a gigantic and fruitful effort had been made, 
which shows that the capabilities and combat readiness of our 
Armed Forces have been strengthened. 
  Another important point analyzed was the FAR's 
[Revolutionary 
Armed Forces] agricultural-livestock activity toward the goal of 
supplying all the troops with food; a 30-percent increase toward 
achieving this objective is expected this year. 
  During the Minfar's expanded military council, on the 
occasion of his 50th anniversary as a combat pilot, Enrique 
Carrera [last name as heard], hero of the Republic of Cuba, was 
promoted to the rank of division general. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

