<H3> <TI>   Socialists, Workers `Repudiate' Gore's Presence </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2103172394 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
1607 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2103172394 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires,21 Mar (NA) -- Members of the Socialist 
Workers Movement (MST) and the Workers Party (PO) are waiting at 
the entrance of the Sheraton Hotel to "repudiate the presence in 
the country" of U.S. Vice President Albert Gore. 
  Gore arrived in Argentina last night and is now attending 
the 
opening ceremony of the World Telecommunications Conference at 
the Libertador Hall of the Sheraton Hotel in Buenos Aires. 

