<H3> <TI>   Menem, Gore Open World Telecommunications Conference </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2103180794 Buenos Aires Radio Nacional Network in Spanish 
1600 GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2103180794 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires Radio Nacional Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Report by Gaston Sulage from the Sheraton Hotel in Buenos </F>
Aires -- live] 
  [Text] The First World Conference on Telecommunications 
Development, organized by International Telecommunications 
Union, has just been opened. U.S. Vice President Albert Gore 
and President Carlos Menem gave addresses. 
  Al Gore thanked Argentina for hosting this conference with 
such a magnificent level of hospitality -- referring to Menem -- 
and asked everyone to help him create a global infrastructure of 
information. He added that information is a treasure which must 
be shared if it is to be of true value. 
  Let us now go to an excerpt of Menem's address: 
  [Begin Menem recording] As Argentines, Argentines who are 
doubly proud. First for the distinction of having been chosen 
to host this conference. Also for the opportunity of showing 
the world our achievements in the arduous task we have 
undertaken, to transform the state and especially the 
privatization and deregulation of the communications sector. 
  It has been an essential step in our policy: To modernize 
the 
country's structure and thus be better armed to confront the 
challenges of the 21st century. 
  We have done all this and will continue, thinking of future 
generations. This why the transformation process being 
implemented avoided every opportunity for speculation. [end 
recording] 
  That was part of Menem's address. He also stated that during 
the course of this conference, a contract will be signed to 
expand the cellular telephone service throughout the country, 
and that a international tender, one of the few examples in the 
world, is about to be issued to resolve the structural problem 
of how to control the radio-electric spectrum. 

</TEXT>

