<H3> <TI>   New International Economic Relations Secretary Appointed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1903174294 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
2248 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1903174294 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 18 Mar (NA) -- The Foreign Ministry 
announced tonight that Jorge Campbell will be sworn in on 20 
March as the new secretary for international economic relations. 
He replaces resigning International Economic Relations 
Secretary Hector Gambarotta. 
  Foreign Minister Guido Di Tella accepted Gambarotta's 
resignation and promptly appointed engineer Jorge Campbell to 
this post. Campbell has headed twice the Foreign Trade 
Undersecretariat, and in 1991 he was appointed head of the 
Integration Undersecretariat in the president's office. 

