<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Students Confront Police at Finance Ministry Demonstration </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1803141594 Madrid EFE in Spanish 2337 GMT 16 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY1803141594 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brasilia, 16 Mar (EFE) -- Police sources have 
reported that two policemen and 12 students were slightly 
wounded when demonstrating students attempted to occupy the 
Finance Ministry in Brasilia today. 
  The incidents began when some 500 students -- who were 
demonstrating against the government's recent economic measures 
and against the constitutional reform in the area of the 
ministry buildings -- arrived at the Finance Ministry building. 
  Instigated by leaders of the National Union of Students 
(UNE), a group of demonstrators attempted to invade the building 
of the ministry, which had promoted the economic measures 
lifting restrictions on the installments paid to private schools 
and universities. 
  For approximately 30 minutes the demonstrators confronted 
200 
military policemen who were guarding the building. A number of 
windows were broken by the stones thrown by the students. 
  Two policemen and 12 students suffered injuries of a minor 
nature, although 8 of the demonstrators did need to be seen at a 
Brasilia area hospital. 

</TEXT>

