<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   3-80 Northern Front Demobilization To Resume </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2103142894 Managua Radio Nicaragua Network in Spanish 1200 
GMT 21 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2103142894 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua Radio Nicaragua Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "This Morning" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Friday after five hours of negotiations between the 
leader of the 3-80 Northern Front and the Government Ministry, 
it was agreed that as of today the demobilization process would 
resume. This process should conclude by 25 March. The final 
disarmament will take place on 8 April taking into account, as 
Government Minister Alfredo Mendieta and rebel leader Jose Angel 
Talavera have reported, the gradual demobilization because some 
details, like acquiring land and implementing emergency 
employment programs for Talavera's demobilized men, have yet to 
be worked out. 
  Government Minister Mendieta reported that a member of the 
Northern Front will join the Interinstitutional Commission 
supervising the rebels disarmament in the country's north. 

</TEXT>

