<F P=100> Peru </F>
<H3> <TI>   Despite Popularity Fujimori Will Not Win In First Round </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2103160394 Lima EXPRESO in Spanish 7 Mar 94 p A6 </F>
<F P=103> PY2103160394 </F>
<F P=104>  Lima EXPRESO </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] President Alberto Fujimori is the favorite 
candidate for the 1995 elections according to a poll conducted 
by the Datum enterprise. 
  The poll reveals that between Fujimori and Javier Perez de 
Cuellar, 35 percent prefer Fujimori and 30 percent Perez de 
Cuellar. 
  The survey also reveals something new: If Fujimori competed 
against an unidentified candidate of the opposition, the latter 
would obtain 36 percent of the votes and Fujimori 39 percent. 
  Even like this, Fujimori would still be 11 points below the 
figure required to, hypothetically, win the first round of 
elections and thus eliminate a second round. 
  The results of the poll, which included a universe of 400 
people of different social levels in Lima and Callao between 26 
February and 1 March, were disclosed yesterday during the 
television program "Contrapunto." 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-11501 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drlat055_r_94001" </HT>


