Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Le Van Triet, Vietnamese minister of commerce and 
tourism, reiterated his country's promise to send 100,000 tons 
of rice during 1994 as part of a cooperation agreement and 
mercantile exchange between the two countries. During a meeting 
with Cuban Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina, the Vietnamese 
minister was optimistic as to the renewal process of the Cuban 
economy and underscored that his country understands the 
importance of maintaining the trade agreement. 
