agriculture and food industry. Both sides expressed their 
satisfaction with the growing atmosphere of mutually beneficial 
cooperation between the two countries. Nguyen Cong Tan came out 
in favor of boosting cooperation not only in agriculture but 
also in, among other spheres, construction, health, education, 
science, biotechnology, and maritime transport. 
  Robaina also met with (Nguyen May), vice chairman of the 
State Commission for Cooperation and Investment, who came out in 
favor of joint enterprises in construction and other areas 
before exploring other fields. 
  Roberto Robaina met with Vietnamese Prime Minister Vo Van 
Kiet. He also held talks with his counterpart, Nguyen Manh Cam. 
Robaina's agenda includes a meeting with the general secretary 
of the Vietnamese Communist Party and a news conference to wind 
up his tour of Asia. 
  Foreign Minister Robaina announced his next tour, in April, 
through Argentina, Uruguay, Peru, Ecuador, Chile, and Paraguay 
and the possibility of visiting Arab countries 

