<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Genie Murder Trail Continues </TI></H3>
<H4>   Further on H. Ortega Testimony </H4>
<F P=102> PA2203192494 Managua Sistema Nacional de Television Network 
in Spanish 0200 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2203192494 </F>
<F P=104>  Managua Sistema Nacional de Television Network 
in Spanish 0200 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>



<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105>Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From the "National" newscast] </F>
  [Text] The military prosecutor in charge of the case of the 
murder of Jean Paul Genie today applied a precautionary measure 
to General Humberto Ortega. 
  Today, Gen. Ortega for the first time presented himself at 
the Military Prosecutor's Office to testify on the case of the 
young Genie. The Army chief testified for more than five hours 
regarding the charges of his alleged responsibility in the Genie 
killing. The general said that on the day Genie died, 28 
October 1990, he was in his residence. He said the Army has 
been supporting the Investigative Commission as a result of 
conversations he has had with other high-ranking officers and in 
response to a request from former Government Minister Carlos 
Hurtado. 
  During the lengthy questioning, the prosecution asked about 
the Army chief's movements and the administrative structure of 
the Army. At the end of the interrogation, Prosecutor Lester 
Gallo ordered precautionary measures against Gen. Ortega. 
  [Begin recording] [Ortega] In my case, having assumed my own 
defense, the precautionary measure ordered by the Military 
Prosecutor's Office is to limit my movements for a lawfully 
established period of time in my home town, which is Managua. 
  [Raymond Genie, father of Jean Paul Genie] As we see it, 
house arrest is not important. The magnitude of the sentence 
must correspond to the magnitude of the crime. These moves are 
aimed at earning much public attention and at producing 
international effects to later shun the matter. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

<DOC>
<DOCNO> FBIS3-11571 </DOCNO>
<HT>    "drlat056_i_94003" </HT>


<HEADER>
<AU>   FBIS-LAT-94-056 </AU>
Document Type:Daily Report 
<DATE1>  22 Mar 1994 </DATE1>

