<F P=100> Nicaragua </F>
<H3> <TI>   Unidentified Gunmen Kidnap, Kill Municipal FSLN Official </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2303001594 Panama City ACAN in Spanish 2318 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> PA2303001594 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City ACAN </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Managua, 22 Mar (ACAN-EFE) -- Unidentified gunmen 
today murdered Cesar Barahona, the Sandinist National Liberation 
Front's [FSLN] political secretary in Wiwili Municipality, near 
the border with Honduras. FSLN sources report that the body of 
Barahona, who was kidnapped yesterday by a group of rebels of 
unknown political affiliation, was found by Army troops in Aguas 
Rojas, some 7 km from Wiwili. 
  Barahona was killed while carrying a list of regional 
delegates who are to participate in the FSLN's special congress 
in May. According to political sources, the activist could have 
been kidnapped and murdered for "being a Sandinist." Police 
have not released any official explanation. 

</TEXT>

