<F P=100> Panama </F>
<H3> <TI>   Labor Union Group Endorses Perez Balladares for President </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2203162994 Panama City LA ESTRELLA DE PANAMA in Spanish 21 
Mar 94 p A1 </F>

<F P=103> PA2203162994 </F>
<F P=104>  Panama City LA ESTRELLA DE PANAMA </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Article by Emilio Sinclair] </F>
  [Text] The National Central Organization of Panamanian 
Workers (CNTP), which comprises three workers' federations and 
16 unions for a total of 12,000 workers, has proclaimed its 
determination to support Dr. Ernesto Perez Balladares for the 
presidency of the Republic. 
  In an "electoral communique" signed by CNTP Secretary 
General 
Luis Cobos R., the organization said it hopes that with this 
decision "we will achieve the return of the Torrijist forces to 
power to stimulate the process of national liberation." 
  The workers' organization also voiced its support for Andres 
Vega Cedeno, also known as "Domplin," a radio commentator who is 
running for mayor of Panama City; and recommended that "the 
workers also vote for Felipe Cano, who is running for mayor of 
San Miguelito." 
  As for the "candidates for 1994-1999 legislators," the CNTP 
recommends that "workers and popular movements support the 
candidates committed to our efforts and suggests the names of 
two candidates from the Papa Egoro Movement: Norma Cano in 
electoral circuit 8.6, and Rolando Miller in circuit 8.9, whom 
the workers describe as "great fighters." [quotation marks as 
published] 
  The CNTP feels that Norma Cano is a "labor leader with vast 
experience," and that Rolando Miller is a union champion "who 
showed ability and honesty in the struggle against the 
neoliberal and persecution policies of the current regime." 

</TEXT>

