<F P=100> SOUTH AMERICA </F>
<F P=101> Argentina </F>
<H3> <TI>   Government Denies Approving Patents Law By Decree </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2203191294 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
1825 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2203191294 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 22 Mar (NA) -- Presidential Secretary 
General Eduardo Bauza categorically denied this afternoon that 
the government plans to promulgate by decree the pharmaceutical 
patents legislation if Congress delays approving the bill now 
being debated in the Senate. 
  "Under no circumstance will that happen" said Bauza, adding 
that the government "trusts" the bill will be approved by the 
Chamber of Deputies "possibly by the middle of this year." 

</TEXT>

