<H3> <TI>   Secretary for Technical, Scientific Affairs Appointed </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2303022494 Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS in Spanish 
2211 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2303022494 </F>
<F P=104>  Buenos Aires NOTICIAS ARGENTINAS </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Buenos Aires, 22 Mar (NA) -- Domingo Liotta, an 
outstanding heart surgeon and General Juan Domingo Peron's 
personal doctor, will replace the late Raul Matera as secretary 
for technical and scientific affairs. 
  In talks with journalists accredited to Government House, 
Liotta announced that this afternoon he accepted President 
Carlos Menem's proposal to become secretary for technical and 
scientific affairs. 
  According to government sources, Liotta will meet Menem at 
Government House at 0800 on 23 March. Liotta reportedly will be 
sworn in at 1100 on 24 March in the White Hall. 

</TEXT>

