<H3> <TI>   Portugal President Soares Arrives for 9-Day Visit </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY1903001494 Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network in Portuguese 
2200 GMT 18 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY1903001494 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Voz do Brasil Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Portuguese President Mario Soares arrived in Rio de 
Janeiro today. He will start the first leg of his nine-day visit 
to the country. He said that the country has progressed since 
his last visit last year, adding that he trusts the new economic 
plan will succeed. 
  President Mario Soares expressed support for the proposal by 
Ambassador Jose Aparecido to create a community of 
Portuguese-speaking countries. 
  The Portuguese president also will visit Curitiba, Bahia, 
and 
Minas Gerais. 

</TEXT>

