<H3> <TI>   Havana Cites Clinton on Retaining Embargo </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2203182294 Havana Radio Rebelde Network in Spanish 1255 
GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2203182294 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Radio Rebelde Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Speaking last night at a dinner to collect funds for 
his Democratic Party -- which garnered more than $3 million -- 
U.S. President William Clinton said he will not lift the 
blockade on Cuba. During the dinner, Clinton seemed worried 
about the fact that he will have to testify again before the 
special prosecutor in the Whitewater case. [Former] Judge David 
Hale had said that through transactions Clinton provided some 
$100,000 to the Whitewater company, through which Clinton and 
his wife Hilary owned some properties when Clinton was governor 
of Arkansas. 

