<F P=100> Suriname </F>
<H3> <TI>   Threatening Rebel Gunmen Release Hostages </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  AU2403100394 Paris AFP in English 0957 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> AU2403100394 </F>
<F P=104>  Paris AFP </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The Hague, 24 March (AFP) -- Suriname rebels 
threatening to blow up a hydroelectric dam freed all their 
hostages unharmed overnight, the Dutch news agency ANP reported. 
  The announcement came after the rebels freed four of their 
30 
hostages Wednesday. About 100 gunmen from a previously unknown 
Suriname Liberation Front stormed the dam site at Afaboka on 
Monday, demanding that President Ronald Venetiaan and his 
government resign and hand over to the national assembly. 

</TEXT>

