<H3> <TI>   Central Information Office Head Comments </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PA2303155394 Caracas Venezolana de Television Network in 
Spanish 2350 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2303155394 </F>
<F P=104>  Caracas Venezolana de Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [From "The News" newscast] </F>
  [Text] Central Information Office Minister [title as 
heard] Guillermo Alvarez Bajares said the Democratic Action [AD] 
proposal for a special powers law is interesting. He added, 
however, that it remains to be seen what methods will be used to 
reach a consensus in the legislature to approve the proposal. 
  Alvarez Bajares believes the measure would expedite the 
implementation of certain laws that must be applied quickly if 
they are to accomplish the intended objectives. 
  [Begin Alvarez Bajares recording] The AD proposal refers to 
the truly difficult situation the country is experiencing. We 
want to interpret this proposal with the utmost good faith in 
the sense that it can contribute to the expediency of 
decisionmaking and therefore speed up the process to solve the 
country's crisis. [end recording] 
  Alvarez Bajares noted that although the AD proposal is 
interesting, the government had at no time considered making 
such a proposal itself. 

</TEXT>

