<F P=100> Bolivia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Former Narcotics Chief Faustino Rico Arrested </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2303203094 La Paz Television Nacional Network in Spanish 
1700 GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2303203094 </F>
<F P=104>  La Paz Television Nacional Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Colonel Faustino Rico Toro was arrested by the 
Special Antinarcotics Force [FELCN] in Cochabamba last night. 
Rico Toro was one of former dictator Luis Garcia Meza's close 
assistants. But he was not tried with the former dictator. 
  He was appointed FELCN commander during Jaime Paz Zamora's 
government, although he had to resign a few hours later after 
observations made by the U.S. Embassy, which had suspicions of 
Rico Toro's links to drug traffickers. 
  His arrest occurred between 2100 and 2300 last night. He is 
being detained at a FELCN jail in Cochabamba. There is evidence 
against him. He is being questioned, FELCN Deputy Commander 
General Rogelio Vargas said. 
  Vargas added that he did not know whether Rico Toro will be 
transferred to La Paz. This is something that must be decided by 
prosecutors, he said. In another 48 hours we will know if the 
Cochabamba prosecutor's office will bring charges of drug 
trafficking against Faustino Rico Toro. If so, he will spend a 
few years in prison. 

</TEXT>

