<F P=102>  FL2303175894 Havana Cuba Vision Network in Spanish 0100 GMT 
23 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2303175894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Cuba Vision Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The annual session of the Chinese People's Congress 
ended today with a call to continue political and economic 
reforms. The 3,000 deputies were urged to work to balance the 
national reforms, development, and stability. 
  Premier Li Peng has warned the United States that China is a 
sovereign country and will not negotiate or agree to anything in 
detriment to its self-determination. Li Peng said he expected 
better results during the visit of U.S. Secretary of State 
Warren Christopher between 11 and 14 March. That trip was 
preceded by a broad campaign against alleged Chinese human 
rights violations, in which Beijing was threatened with 
withdrawal of most favored nation status in bilateral trade. 

