<H3> <TI>   Robaina Continues Vietnam Visit </TI></H3>
<H4>   Visits Ho Chi Minh City </H4>
<F P=102> FL2403032894 Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks in 
Spanish 0100 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2403032894 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Tele Rebelde and Cuba Vision Networks </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Roberto Robaina arrived in Ho Chi 
Minh City today, where he was greeted by Vo Tran Chi, member of 
the Politburo and first secretary of this city's party 
committee. At this meeting, Robaina explained to Vo Tran Chi 
that Cuba is immersed in a process of change in which the 
people's participation is essential. 
  Robaina, who is on the last leg of an Asian tour that 
included eight Southeast Asian countries, pointed out that Cuba 
is making many changes and that there are many still to come. 
Robaina said that Cuba wants to learn first-hand from the 
experiences of a brother such as Vietnam, to which we are linked 
not only by economic ties but by auspicious and frank 
traditional ties. He added that Cuba is in a process of recovery 
that is dependent on the efforts and work of the Cuban people. 
Robaina stressed that what has most caught his attention in 
Vietnam is the way the party controls and directs the economic 
reforms. 
  Vo Tran Chi said that there are many spheres in which the 
two 
countries can hold exchanges with a view to overcoming the 
current circumstances. The Cuban delegation will also meet with 
local officials and tour sites of economic interest. 
  Ho Chi Minh City, which has a population of 5 million, is 
considered Vietnam's most important commercial hub. 

</TEXT>

