<H3> <TI>   Granma Province Testing Bayamo TV Transmission </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2403015694 Havana Cuba Vision Network in Spanish 2320 GMT 
23 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2403015694 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Cuba Vision Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] This is what the television signal broadcast for the 
first time from Granma looked like. This is an old dream of this 
eastern region. Several tests have been conducted, and the 
specialists say that, except for the town of Buey Arriba, the 
signal reaches every municipality in the province strongly. 
Certain antennas have been rotated and others installed, making 
it possible to broadcast the signal from the center of Bayamo. 
Efforts to have a television station in Granma Province, though 
optimistic, have not yet borne fruit, since most of the 
equipment, which comes from abroad, is lacking. 
  Those of you who have seen this signal on your television 
set 
may find it interesting to know that it was broadcast using this 
Television Serrana cassette player or the videotape recorder 
from the office of the NTV correspondent. 
  Work is under way with a view to organizing a first, weekly, 
30-minute program, which will of course be broadcast employing 
the minimal equipment we mentioned. 
  Also, the effort made by the Communications Ministry makes 
it 
possible for Granma Province to receive the signal from 
Holguin's (Tele Cristal) with top quality. 

</TEXT>

