<H3> <TI>   Pope Meets With Visiting Haitian Bishops </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2303125494 Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole in French 1700 
GMT 18 Mar </F>

<F P=103> FL2303125494 </F>
<F P=104>  Port-au-Prince Radio Metropole </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> French </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Excerpt] On Friday, 18 March, Pope John Paul II renewed 
the call for dialogue with all the components of Haitian society 
that he had issued on 15 January. It is up to the Haitians, he 
stated in a speech to the Haitian bishops who came to Rome on 
their quinquennial visit, to build their future based on the 
principles about which you have reminded them recently. The 
pope mentioned in his speech Haiti's numerous problems to which 
are added, he said, the obsessive problems created by the 
political instability and the economic embargo and most of all 
the shattering show of a nation in distress which is struggling 
day after day in order to survive. [passage omitted] 

