<F P=100> MEXICO </F>
<H3> <TI>   Colosio Shot, Killed in Attack During Tijuana Campaign Stop </TI></H3>
<H4>   Salinas: `Odious' Attack </H4>
<F P=102> PA2403040694 Mexico City XEW Television Network in Spanish 
0321 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2403040694 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City XEW Television Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

<F P=106> [Message to the nation by Mexican President Carlos Salinas </F>
de Gortari from Los Pinos presidential palace in Mexico City on 
23 March -- recorded] 
  [Text] Compatriots, a few minutes ago an odious attack was 
carried out against Luis Donaldo Colosio. It is an action that 
deeply hurts us, and me particularly, because this is an attack 
on a human being. In addition, it is against a noble man, a 
good man, who seeks to serve others and to serve his country. I 
have already heard many voices express their consternation with 
this incident and their all-out rejection of this attack. I am 
in constant contact to learn about Colosio's condition. I have 
sent my sympathy to his family. I have sent my personal 
physician and an expert to help the doctors attending him. 
  I have been informed that arrests have been made. I have 
given instructions to the attorney general to travel to Tijuana 
to help in the investigation. We will get to the bottom of this 
and the full weight of the law shall be applied. 
  The most important thing right now is Luis Donaldo Colosio's 
health. I am certain that if we all join in our sentiments of 
compassion and serenity and direct them positively, it will be 
good for him and good for all of us. Personally, this is a very 
painful matter, as he is a beloved Mexican. I offer him and his 
family all my affection and warmth. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

