<H4>   24 March Day of Mourning </H4>
<F P=102> PA2403123994 Mexico City Radio ACIR Network in Spanish 1215 
GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PA2403123994 </F>
<F P=104>  Mexico City Radio ACIR Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] At approximately 0515, President Salinas de Gortari 
decreed that Thursday, 24 March, will be a day of national 
mourning. All Mexican flags will fly half-mast at public 
buildings, schools, banks, and at all municipal palaces in 
Mexican towns as a sign of mourning over the death of Luis 
Donaldo Colosio. 

</TEXT>

