<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Political, Military Figures Comment on Wage Increase </TI></H3>
<H4>   Possible Salary Deterioration Protested </H4>
<F P=102> PY2403010794 Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television in 
Portuguese 2300 GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2403010794 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Here is a report on the national day of protest 
against possible salary deterioration caused by the economic 
plan. The strike called by the labor centrals ended up as a set 
of sporadic demonstrations. 
  The Sao Paulo subway began operating this morning at 0700, 
two hours later than normal. A demonstration by bus drivers and 
ticket collectors caused a traffic jam on Celso Garcia Avenue, 
one of the most important avenues in eastern Sao Paulo. 
  In downtown Sao Paulo, retired bank employees protested 
ironically, asking for donations for the deputies who increased 
their own salaries. 
  Sao Paulo industrial belt metalworkers blocked the Anchieta 
highway, which joins Sao Paulo and the sea coast, in protest 
against the Volkswagen truck factory. 
  In the afternoon, bank employees, chemical industry workers, 
and taxi drivers staged a motorade along Paulista Avenue. 
  In Brasilia, public servants march along the ministries' 
esplanade. The police guard was reinforced. The march ended 
with a demonstration in front of the Finance Ministry building. 

</TEXT>

