<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Political, Military Figures Comment on Wage Increase </TI></H3>
<H4>   Galotti Criticizes `Improper Government Meddling' </H4>
<F P=102> PY2403004994 Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television in 
Portuguese 2300 GMT 23 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2403004994 </F>
<F P=104>  Rio de Janeiro Rede Globo Television </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Supreme Federal Court President Otavio Galotti 
criticized what he called improper government meddling in 
Judicial Branch accounts. 
  When Supreme Court justices arrived for today's plenary 
session, they declined to talk about salaries. But before the 
session they held a meeting under the protection of guards. This 
delayed the beginning of the session for almost an hour. 
  During the session, Galotti again read a note released on 21 
March saying the Supreme Court rejects the crude and 
unacceptable insults against the court and its members. 
  Galotti once again explained that salaries were converted to 
the URV [Real Value Unit] on 20 March because judicial branch 
members are paid their salaries on the 20th of each month. 
According to him, this measure caused no salary increase and 
served only to prevent losses from the conversion. 
  Galotti harshly criticized the government decision to cancel 
the 10.9 percent adjustment of the salaries paid today. 
  Attorney General Aristides Junqueira, who is attending the 
Supreme Court meetings, said after the session that the 
conversion is a 10-percent problem that is jeopardizing 
Brazilian institutions, and that this is unbelievable. 
  Junqueira added that the solution is to modify the law and, 
to this end, representatives of the three branches of government 
are negotiating. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

