<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Castro Sends Condolences to President Salinas </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  FL2503021194 Havana Cuba Vision Network in Spanish 0100 GMT 
25 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2503021194 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Cuba Vision Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] On 24 March, Cuban President Fidel Castro condemned 
the assassination of Luis Donaldo Colosio, presidential 
candidate for the Institutional Revolutionary Party of Mexico. 
This is the full text of the message sent by Castro to Mexican 
President Carlos Salinas de Gortari: 
  Your Excellency Carlos Salinas de Gortari, president of the 
United States of Mexico: 
  Your Excellency: Deeply moved by the tragic news of the 
attack and death of Luis Donaldo Colosio, presidential candidate 
of the Institutional Revolutionary Party, I write to you to 
express our consternation, pain, and condemnation of such an 
unjustifiable act. In this difficult and bitter moment for 
Mexico, we hope this brotherly people will find all the wisdom, 
serenity, and energy necessary to overcome the difficulties and 
leave behind this hard and crucial test of history. 
  I beg of you to convey to the widow, children, and other 
relatives of Luis Donaldo Colosio our most sincere condolences. 
To you and the Mexican people, our most sincere feelings of 
friendship. 
  [Signed] Fidel Castro Ruz, president of the Council of State 
and the Government of the Republic of Cuba. 

</TEXT>

