<F P=100> CARIBBEAN </F>
<F P=101> Cuba </F>
<H3> <TI>   Ross Attends Worker Assembly Plenums </TI></H3>
<H4>   Chairs Plenum Closing in Matanzas </H4>
<F P=102> FL2503031794 Havana Cuba Vision Network in Spanish 0100 GMT 
25 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> FL2503031794 </F>
<F P=104>  Havana Cuba Vision Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] As in the rest of Cuba, the Parliaments in the 
Workplace have concluded in Matanzas Province. Each of the 
proposals and suggestions made by the workers during the 
sessions of the Parliaments in the Workplace will be taken into 
account and will receive an appropriate reply by the union 
leaders of the various sectors involved in the meetings. 
  This was confirmed by Pedro Ross Leal, secretary general of 
the Cuban Workers Federation [CTC], during his address in the 
meeting closing the process in Matanzas. Yadira Garcia, 
Politburo member and first secretary of the Communist Party of 
Cuba in Matanzas, also chaired the meeting. 
  Ross announced that on 29 March the CTC National Committee 
will meet officially to close the nationwide process. Topics 
such as profitability, economic efficiency, subsidies, and 
possible measures to prevent excess currency were issues 
discussed by the 205,000 workers in the province who 
participated in the base meetings, where more than 9,400 
interventions were recorded. Both figures represent a record for 
union meetings in this providence. 
  Ross added that Cuba is looking for a consensus on, 
understanding of, and comprehension of a package of possible 
measures to be implemented, some of which are controversial such 
as the change of currency, an issue on which there are many 
opinions. There are other measures being endorsed by most of the 
population, such as the confiscation of ill-gotten money. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

