<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   Franco Sends Condolences to Mexican Counterpart </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2403235294 Madrid EFE in Spanish 2205 GMT 24 Mar 94 </F>
<F P=103> PY2403235294 </F>
<F P=104>  Madrid EFE </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Spanish </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Brasilia, 24 Mar (EFE) -- Official sources reported 
that Brazilian President Itamar Franco today expressed his 
condolences to his Mexican counterpart, Carlos Salinas de 
Gortari, for the death of Mexican presidential candidate Luis 
Donaldo Colosio. 
  In a fax addressed to Salinas de Gortari, Franco repudiated 
"the absurd and shocking violence" that cost Colosio's life 
while he was presiding over a meeting of his campaign for 
Mexico's presidency for the ruling Institutional Revolutionary 
Party. 
  The Brazilian president hoped Mexico can continue its effort 
to consolidate its economic and social development with the 
support of the democratic institutions. 

</TEXT>

