<F P=100> Brazil </F>
<H3> <TI>   PMDB, PDT To Form Broad Front for Elections </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  PY2203141994 Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network in 
Portuguese 1000 GMT 22 Mar 94 </F>

<F P=103> PY2203141994 </F>
<F P=104>  Brasilia Radio Nacional da Amazonia Network </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> Portuguese </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] The PDT [Democratic Labor Party] and the PMDB 
[Brazilian Democratic Movement Party] are negotiating a broad 
front for the upcoming presidential elections. PDT Deputy 
Vivaldo Barbosa said the two parties are concerned about the 
polarization of the candidacies of Luis Inacio Lula da Silva 
from the PT [Workers Party] and Fernando Henrique Cardoso from 
the PSDB [Brazilian Social Democracy Party]. Barbosa said the 
PDT and the PMDB want to present a new alternative through a 
center-left candidate. 
  One month ago, Rio de Janeiro Governor Leonel Brizola, from 
the PDT, promised PMDB President Luiz Henrique that he will not 
oppose the creation of a progressive broad front. 
  Sao Paulo Governor Luiz Antonio Fleury Filho said that after 
consulting the grassroots, the general wish is to support the 
candidacy of Orestes Quercia as the presidential candidate. 
Fleury revealed that he will campaign for Quercia in all states. 
  The official announcement will be made on 24 March at the 
Sao 
Paulo Government House during a ceremony in which Quercia and 
other Sao Paulo State mayors will be present. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

